rase of the same concept.\n\nLooking at the 特徴 section, it does mention the API approach, so the knowledge file is synthesizing information from multiple parts of the source rather than fabricating. This feels like acceptable cross-referencing rather than a critical error, so I won't flag it.\n\nThe only real issue I'm finding is that s3 has an empty title but contains introductory text that should probably be labeled.\n\nI'm also noticing that s4 and s6 have their titles misaligned with their content—s4's title applies to the code block when it should apply to the note, and s6's title doesn't match the subsection content it actually contains. These are both minor structural problems.\n\nLet me verify I haven't missed any major omissions or inaccuracies by checking the source against what's covered. The key features like transaction control, the @Before/@After annotation note, Excel file path conventions, and the table structure are all accounted for in the sections.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20839,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20839,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a27170b9-227c-4600-8056-039144f5bfff","uuid":"2b2e774a-1922-4c88-8055-c0da0f208faa"}
